            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Ok, this part of behavior wasn't documented in vim.\n\nWhen user enters in insert mode vim's function `init_prompt` checks is current line contains prompt signature. If it's not it tries to append to current buffer and ignores previous lines https://github.com/vim/vim/blob/master/src/job.c#L1640\nCurrent neovim's implementation acts differently and before https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/286371b4d22a0abd3c037823ae14ef7ce8ba06b6 commit that's wasn't the case.\n\nDo I understand correctly that with the advent of the multiline-prompt feature, there is no easy way to bring this  vim's quirk back?\n",
