            "body": "Actually I see a problem. There are plugins out there that don't expect multi-line input so they would still append to `line(\"$\") - 1`. But those plugins will not work as expected if users enter multi-line even accidentally. I think Nvim should make the multi-line feature opt-in (via an option, whatever) in a minor version before making it default and removing single-line mode, so that plugins have time to update their code? @justinmk",
